  <exercise label="cond_rec_a1">
    <statement>
      <p>Fix the code below so that it prints <q>THE TEAM</q> <q>THE TEAM</q>
                    <q>THE TEAM</q> on three
        separate lines.</p>
    </statement>
    <program interactive="activecode"
             line-numbers="yes"
             xml:id="cond_rec_a1q_editor">
        <input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
  int x = 8;
  int y = 8;

  if (x % 2 == 0) {
      cout << "THE TEAM";
  }
  else if (x >= y) {
      cout << "THE TEAM";
  }
  else if (y >= x) {
      cout << "THE TEAM";
  }
}
          ]]></input>
      </program>
    <solution>
      <p>Below is one way to fix the program. Since we want <q>THE TEAM</q> to print three times, we
        must check all three conditons. this means changing the else if statements to if statements.</p>
      <program xml:id="cond_rec_a1_a_editor-1"
               interactive="activecode"
               line-numbers="yes">
          <input><![CDATA[
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
   int x = 8;
   int y = 8;

   if (x % 2 == 0) {
       cout << "THE TEAM" << endl;
   }
   if (x >= y) {
       cout << "THE TEAM" << endl;
   }
   if (y >= x) {
       cout <<< "THE TEAM" << endl;
   }
}
]]></input>
        </program>
    </solution>
  </exercise>

